es.csic.iiia.nsm.agent.language

Class TaxonomyOfNaturalNumbers

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.csic.iiia.nsm.agent.language.TaxonomyOfNaturalNumbers
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Taxonomy

    public class TaxonomyOfNaturalNumbers
extends java.lang.Object
implements Taxonomy
    The taxonomy of natural numbers. This taxonomy consists of all natural numbers from -infinite to +infinite, all of them generalised by term "any". Thus, a pair of two random natural numbers may be generalised to term "any"
    Author:
    "Javier Morales (jmorales@iiia.csic.es)"
    See Also:
    Taxonomy

      • getGeneralisationLevel

        public int getGeneralisationLevel(java.lang.String term)
        Returns the level of generalisation of the given term in the taxonomy (i.e., the domain), always that term is a natural number. If term is a natural number, then it is a leaf in the taxonomy, and hence this method returns 0 (generalisation level 0). If the term equals to "any", then its generalisation level is 1. Otherwise, the term does not belong to the taxonomy and then the method returns -1.
        Specified by:
        getGeneralisationLevel in interface Taxonomy
        Parameters:
        term - the term
        Returns:
        0 if term is a natural number, 1 if term is "any", and -1 otherwise (since the term does not belong to the taxonomy)

      • isTop
